title: I feel like they don’t need ads anymore..
text:
Subway Surfers seems like a well off game. Some people buy their skins and hoverboards, some people constantly choose to play their ads, like after they die or for a prize. So I just don’t get the deal with ads on this game. Like sometimes I choose to watch an ad and then after that I get another ad. I’ve paid this game money before so I know they don’t depend on the forced ads, yet they still do it. 

Anyways, other than that, I love it.

title: Hello!
text: Subway Surfers is an exhilarating endless runner game that captivates players with its vibrant graphics, fast-paced gameplay, and addictive challenges. Its intuitive swipe controls make it accessible to players of all ages, while the variety of characters, hoverboards, and power-ups keep the experience fresh and exciting. One of the game’s strengths lies in its ever-changing landscapes, offering diverse settings from bustling city streets to exotic locations around the world. To enhance the gameplay experience, players can focus on mastering the timing of their jumps and swipes to maximize their score and avoid obstacles more efficiently. Additionally, incorporating more interactive elements, such as customizable characters or daily challenges, could further engage players and add depth to the gameplay. Ultimately, Subway Surfers continues to captivate audiences with its dynamic gameplay and has the potential to further improve with additional features and challenges. THERE IS ALWAYS ROOM TO IMPROVE  💓
